author: AceShowbiz.com
title: Taylor Swift Sizzles in Her First GQ Cover
text:
Comments The 'Bad Blood' hitmaker looks smoking hot as she is featured front and center on GQ's November edition. 
Taylor Swift lands her first ever GQ cover. The 25-year-old country/pop singer graces the front page of the magazine's November issue, showing off her slim figure and toned legs in a form-fitting dress. She sports wavy hair and a natural makeup. "My first GQ cover!" the chart-topping musician gushed and shared the picture on Instagram. "Thanks to GQ and everyone involved. Photos by Michael Thompson. Full story by Chuck Klosterman comes out next week." A photo posted by Taylor Swift (@taylorswift) on Oct 8, 2015 at 8:03am PDT In introducing the mag's newest cover girl, Klosterman wrote, "If you don't take Swift seriously, you don't take contemporary music seriously ... There's simply no antecedent for this kind of career: a cross-genre, youth-oriented, critically acclaimed colossus based entirely on the intuitive songwriting merits of a single female artist. It's as if mid-period Garth Brooks was also early Liz Phair, minus the hat and the swearing. As a phenomenon, it's absolutely new."
